# Redunsy coding standards

## Paradigm

- Use only functional programming: no classes, no `this`, no mutable shared state outside stores.
- Prefer React hooks for component state and side effects.
- Encapsulate features under `features/<feature-name>/` with colocated store, hooks, and UI.

## Style (not fully enforceable in ESLint)

- Prefer arrow functions for all functions and callbacks.
- Prefer concise arrow auto-return (`() => value`) when the body is a single expression.
- Avoid barrel `index` files; import from concrete module paths.
- Keep files under 100 lines when possible; stay under 200 lines unless well justified.

## Structure

- `lib/` — shared non-UI utilities (e.g. `lib/midinike`).
- `features/shared/` — cross-feature client providers and primitives.
- `features/store/` — app-wide Zustand stores.
- `features/<feature>/` — feature modules (`*.store.ts`, component modules).